Package: Dimodal
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2025-11-20
Title: Spacing Tests for Multi-Modality
Authors@R: c(person("Greg", "Kreider", role=c("aut","cre"),
        email="support@primachvis.com"), person("Melissa", "O'Neill",
        role=c("cph")), person("Primordial Machine Vision Systems,
        Inc.", role=c("cph"), email="support@primachvis.com"))
Copyright: Primordial Machine Vision Systems, Inc.
Maintainer: Greg Kreider <support@primachvis.com>
Description: Tests for modality of data using its spacing.  The main
        approach evaluates features (peaks, flats) using a combination
        of parametric models and non-parametric tests, either after
        smoothing the spacing by a low-pass filter or by looking over
        larger intervals.  The library can also use any changepoint
        detectors available to look for transitions between features in
        the spacing.  The Suggested list of libraries is misnamed.  It
        contains all supported changepoint detectors, and all are
        considered optional.  A good minimal set would be the first
        three entries.  Some of the suggestions may no longer be
        current on CRAN, with the last source tarball found in its
        archives or at the additional repository.  These packages will
        be used if they are already installed on older installations,
        but will not be available to newer.
